The paper discusses the use of BERT QA models in biomedical question answering, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), making cs.CL and cs.IR the most likely categories. The paper also investigates the impact of error propagation in end-to-end retrieval and QA systems, which involves machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a likely category as well. The use of BERT models also involves deep learning (DL) and large-scale machine learning (LSML), making cs.LG a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with biomedical data, which could fall under the category of computational biology (cs.CY).
